\f0\b\fs66 \cf0 Baked Apple with Crisp Topping\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs40 \cf2 Yield:  \cf0 4 servings
\b \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa240\ql\qnatural

\fs52 \cf0 INGREDIENTS\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl260\sa280\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\b0\fs48 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}2 apples (recommended: Fuji or McIntosh)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon lemon juice\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup strawberry jam, jelly or preserves\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoon all-purpose flour\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 tablespoons butter, cold and diced\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl260\sa280\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}3 tablespoons brown sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup oats, uncooked\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon\
{\listtext	\'95	}Pinch salt\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b\fs52 \cf0 DIRECTIONS\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa160\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs48 \cf3 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. \uc0\u8232 Cut each apple in half along its equator. Using a melon baller, cut out each side of the core, creating a rounded hole. Rub exposed apple flesh with lemon juice. Place 1 tablespoon of jam into each hole. For the topping: in a small bowl mix together flour, butter, brown sugar, oats, cinnamon and salt. Press this mixture on the top of each apple, covering jam. Place in a baking dish filled with about a 1/4-inch of water. Bake until top is golden brown and apple is tender, about 35 to 40 minutes.\
